  "texts": [
    "This kind of system requires a twofold validation based on both qualitative and quantitative aspects.",
    "For this reason, to evaluate the effectiveness of BPLLM in helping users understand business processes, we designed an experiment covering these two different perspectives.More precisely, the quantitative validation covers the correctness (in terms of accuracy) of the answers with respect to the entities and relationships that are both in the model provided by the user and in the LLM answer.Conversely, the qualitative validation is based on the analysis from the usereffectiveness standpoint of experts judging the effectiveness of answers.",
    "We elaborate on both these aspects formalizing the process.The conclusion drawn from the study focuses on the overall utility of the BPLLM system in aiding business process users, discussing its potential applications in realworld settings.",
    "Based on the outcomes of this experiment, recommendations for system improvements are suggested, along with proposals for further studies to continue validating and enhancing the system's capabilities.In the following, both quantitative and qualitative aspects are discussed.",
    "Quantitative evaluationDifferent experiments are proposed in this section to answer the research questions reported in Section 1."
